<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-78-0584 </DOCNO><TEXT>After an introduction of the principles of the construction appropriatefor the material involved, it is shown with examples which consequencesfor construction should have the realization of these principles in thedesign of ceramic material. With the focal point on construction conceptsfor high temperature heat exchangers for the utilization of solar energy,solution concepts are discussed exemplary. One of the three concepts,for which production and test results are available, is described indetail.</TEXT></DOC>